{'sentence': 'As Liboiron points out, these metaphors are rooted in coloniality.', 'index': 10, 'combined_sentence': 'Exploring the concept of “firsting” in theory building and academic inquiry, Lauren Beck positions it as “the process through which a scholar presents an act, circumstance, or phenomenon generated by [a hu]man, or accomplishment to have occurred for the first time.” Max Liboiron describes firsting as endemic in academia, where students are trained to “stake out” their research areas and “claim” their territory. As Liboiron points out, these metaphors are rooted in coloniality. Firsting is a form of terra nullius.'}
